$ cat /etc/os-release
$ cat /etc/redhat-release --> only works in redhat machine

=================
Using LSB tool to Show System info
1. Install the module LSB:  
    yum install redhat-lsb-core

2. lsb_release -a  --> Display 


==============

To find the hostname:

$ hostnamectl --> Shows host info
$ hostname --> Shows hostname
$ uname --> Shows the kernel release
$ uptime --> Uptime of the server
$ dmesg -H --> Display or control the kernel ring buffer in human readable version
$ free -m --> Display amount of free memory in system






